Package: dvipdfm
Version: 0.13.2c
Revision: 7
Depends: tetex-base (>= 1.0-12), libpng-shlibs
GCC: 3.1
Conflicts: system-tetex
BuildDepends: libpng (>= 1.0.12-3)
Recommends: ghostscript | ghostscript6
Source: http://gaspra.kettering.edu/dvipdfm/dvipdfm-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 82c2113261fad5c7f48d96c4515b731b
SourceDirectory: dvipdfm
SetCPPFLAGS: -no-cpp-precomp
ConfigureParams: --mandir='${prefix}/share/man'
InstallScript: <<
 make install prefix=%i
 mkdir -p %i/etc
 mv %i/share/texmf %i/etc/texmf.local
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/dvipdfm/latex-support
 (cd latex-support; install -p -m 644 *.* %i/share/doc/dvipdfm/latex-support)
 mkdir -p %i/etc/texmf.local/tex/latex/graphics
 mv %i/share/doc/dvipdfm/latex-support/dvipdfm.def %i/etc/texmf.local/tex/latex/graphics/dvipdfm.def.dvipdfm
<<
DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING Credits INSTALL INSTALL-BINARY NEWS OBTAINING README README.FIRST TODO doc/*.* 
ConfFiles: %p/etc/texmf.local/dvipdfm/config/config
PostInstScript: if [ -f %p/bin/mktexlsr ]; then mktexlsr %p/etc/texmf.local; fi
PostRmScript: if [ -f %p/bin/mktexlsr ]; then mktexlsr %p/etc/texmf.local; fi
License: GPL
Description: Produce PDF files directly from DVI files
DescUsage: <<
You may wish to edit the configuration file
  %p/share/texmf/dvipdfm/config/config
to fit your local circumstances.
<<
